$interpreted: Lizard Soldier: Get in line! Take out your travel papers and present yourselves in an orderly fashion! Any funny business and I'll have you dropped in the ocean!
Eastern Refugee: Nooo! We're all lined up, see!
Lizard Soldier: Really, I don't know who could stand for letting in so many people. What on earth is the Queen thinking...
Puggi: Wowee, that's a lotta people!
Hestia: Yeah, looks like Pang was right. Everybody's fleeing from the monsters in the East!
Puggi: So Pang drove us out so that we could take cover at Maple Lake?
Puggi: ...I thought he just wanted to get rid of us so he'd be free to go chasing after girls...
Hestia: I told you, we have to trust him! The Insects have nearly won, and he's gone back to the Tiger Tribe to help his people!
Hestia: So many people... Pang must have fought hard to get us a ticket for the boat.
Puggi: ...I misunderstood you, brother. Looks like you were keeping us free of danger all along...
Hestia: What are you on about now...
Desert Merchant: You're so annoying! I told you I don't know, go bother someone else!
???: Please, think a little harder! It looks like a chubby bird with a croissant on its head...
Desert Merchant: I've got it. It's a legendarily delicious creature, eaten to extinction long ago. So no, I've never seen one!
Hestia: Sounds like that girl's looking for you, Puggi...
Hestia: Hey, what are you hiding for? That's not like you. I thought you'd yell out "Just my type!" and strut right over there...
Puggi: Hm, hmm, hmmm, hmmmmmm...
Hestia: Puggi?
Puggi: You underestimate me. As the heroic MC of Season 4, I'd never fail to recognize such a familiar scene, all set up just for me...
Puggi: That's right! I see right through the trap you've set here! If I weren't so careful I might have ended up as someone's dinner!
Hestia: Ehh? You mean... That girl's looking for you, because she wants to eat you?
Hestia: Oh come on, you're just being paranoid—
???: But the latest edition of the Red Velvet Guide clearly states that someone in a desert port witnessed—
Desert Merchant: What's wrong with you!? They're totally extinct now, who cares what your gourmet guide says!
Puggi: ......
Hestia: ...Seems she wants to eat you after all, Puggi...
???: I know there's monsters, but... but! It's my lifelong dream to eat such a legendary, delicious creature!
???: I've worked so hard to leave home... and I've come so far. This might be the only chance I ever get...!
Desert Merchant: That's your business, not mine—and I don't even dare to do mine anymore. I've just got to get out of here!
Desert Merchant: Scram, you're holding up the line!
Eastern Refugee: Aaahh! Somebody's fallen in!
Hestia: Uh oh! I'll save her!
???: *splutter*... *cough*...
???: Gah... the water's too damn salty here, it tastes awful... The spring water of the East goes down a bit better...
Hestia: Get a grip, you almost drowned just then~ You really live through your stomach! Are you all right?
???: Ah, I'm sorry. I got a little carried away...
???: I'm Gretta. Thanks for saving me~
Hestia: I'm Hestia, and that's Puggi~
Puggi: (Wowee, she's even prettier from close up...)
Puggi: Nice try... b-b-but you won't trick me that easily!
Gretta: Huh? Who's trying to trick you? That said, your head looks just like...
Hestia: I-ignore him! Puggi just loves talking nonsense! Hahaha!
Desert Soldier: You lot!
Desert Soldier: Tell me, was this the guy that pushed her into the water?
Desert Merchant: I-I-I didn't do it on purpose, I just pushed a little too hard and...
Gretta: It was my fault, I wasn't watching where I was going.
Hestia: I clearly saw this guy—
Gretta: I lose all self-awareness as soon as I smell anything tasty. I'm sorry, I must have really been bothering you just now.
Desert Merchant: What baloney... uh, I mean, no worries...
Gretta: He's not the only one. These past few days I've been following my Red Velvet Guide and asking all over the place, without a thought for anyone else.
Gretta: I'm feeling a little clearer now, thanks to that dip in the ocean... I really do apologize.
Eastern Refugee: Oh come on, it was annoying, but not THAT annoying...
Hestia: So she's been here for several days already? She's really crazy about chowing down on that legendary dish, huh~
Puggi: Ah, what a nice young lady~ Having a passion for something is ever so charming...
Puggi: No! I won't be fooled!! I'm warning you, Screenwriter, don't mess with me!
Lizard Sailor: Hyaaah!
Pirate: Harhar! Get yerselves in line, ya great ship o' fools, it's payday!
Pirate: Hurry up 'n' hand over all yer trinkets and gewgaws!
Desert Merchant: Hey! Aren't you supposed to be soldiers!? The pirates are making landfall!
Lizard Soldier: We're too busy with these refugees to be on patrol! We told you it was too many people to let in, you big dummy Queen!
Pirate: Take out yer cash if ye don't wanna end up just like this laddy!
Desert Merchant: H-help! Somebody save us...
Gretta: That's my cue. Let this be my way of making up to everyone.
Hestia: Hey, are you sure about this!?
Puggi: The MC never hides his true identity when there's a damsel in distress. Let's get out there!
Pirate: So ye can conjure frosts and snows... and that jewel...
Pirate: Y-ye... Nay, yer a witch...!
Gretta: Hush.
Gretta: Thanks for all your help, I must be off~ I'm famished after such a fight!
Hestia: You're leaving? But the ships aren't running anymore!?
Gretta: Let's go. You may be a pirate, but a lad from the North like you surely wouldn't mind taking me home?
Hestia: Watch out! Don't get too close to them, they're pirates...
Pirate: ...We're anchored right there, find yer own...
Pirate: Oh, uh, I mean... Right this way.
Gretta: ...How I wanna have just one taste of such a legendary, delicious creature... Next time... Yeah, next time I'll have a bite of you for sure!
